UPDATE consultations SET notes = '{"subjective":"Maggie presents for ear infection in one ear","objective":"Ceruminous debris \nOdor\nPruritis in ear","assessment":"Otitis media bacteria and yeast most likely a mixed infection","plan":"Called in broad spectrum Posatex treatment to chewy to be treated with 8 drops per day once daily for 7 days \nOther recommended treatment is Triz Ultra keto ear flush which can be ordered from chewy to be used once a day per first 7 days before drops and then weekly there after for prevention"}', updated_at = unixepoch() WHERE id = '0vltdGmIcjmW44xQoxfN';
UPDATE consultations SET notes = '{"subjective":"Daisy is a mini who presents for virtual consultation on recommendations for her sudden onset respiratory issue","objective":"Stertor versus strider \nSudden onset audible wheezing","assessment":"Sudden onset \n\nUpper versus lower airway disease rule out\n\nPotential asthma \nPotential tracheal issue\nPotential obstruction \nPotential allergic reaction","plan":"Plan is for referral to have a respiratory work up and potential x rays, ultrasound, or airway scoping \n\nI spoke to a few intern large animal specialist and sent your video to them: \n\nThey are all giving the recommendation for her to be worked up and transported to a referral hospital instead of trying steroids due to the risk of laminitis (long term lameness issues) \n\nThe discussion is surrounding if it’s lower airway or upper airway disease and they are recommending she get scoped, where a camera assesses her airway and tells us what is going on.\n\nThey said if we aren’t 100 percent sure it’s asthma we could make things worse by “trying steroids”. Which in virtual medicine we aren’t sure. They said it’s not that it isn’t possible to be asthma but to happen overnight and this be a problem she’s never had previously they’re more concerned it’s something else going on and needs more diagnostics \n\nTruly the only referral hospitals I would trust would be in Ocala and you need to trailer there. \n\nIf this is something you would consider there are 3 referral hospitals I would recommend\n\nEquine medical center of Ocala \n\n\nOcala equine hospital \n\n\nPeterson and smith \n\nEquine wellness and performance with Dr. Beigel is another option for\nMobile equine veterinary care in Brevard county \n\n\nThey are all great. But maybe tomorrow you could call and get an estimate of working up airway disease in a mini with diagnostics such as scoping and see who offers the soonest appointment and what the cost is"}', updated_at = unixepoch() WHERE id = '1w6IiOwgPVsKQpN3yqdZ';
